1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,980
So we do, like, a lot of serve and passing reception.

2
00:00:04,299 --> 00:00:05,259
Like, we just do a lot.

3
00:00:05,360 --> 00:00:06,080
It's important.

4
00:00:06,280 --> 00:00:09,019
Our serve for us is one of the biggest, like, points of our game

5
00:00:09,019 --> 00:00:11,919
where I like to distinguish us from other teams.

6
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:13,619
And so we do a lot of this.

7
00:00:13,660 --> 00:00:15,539
This is just called set a better.

8
00:00:15,699 --> 00:00:17,660
So it's a three-big-point game.

9
00:00:17,839 --> 00:00:21,500
Basically, the whole reception is working as a group

10
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:23,320
and the whole serve is working as a group.

11
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:27,300
So you've got to get three good receptions in a row to get a big point

12
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:30,059
or you've got to get three good serves in a row to get a big point.

13
00:00:30,940 --> 00:00:34,479
However, I'm adding on top of this set a better.

14
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:38,159
So if it's a good pass, a good reception, and the setter gets it in,

15
00:00:39,899 --> 00:00:44,619
then confirmed, you get your, like, reception point.

16
00:00:44,880 --> 00:00:46,939
If they miss, then it becomes a serve point.

17
00:00:47,799 --> 00:00:51,619
And if they get a ball in that is not a good pass,

18
00:00:51,780 --> 00:00:53,179
then you upgrade it to a good point.

19
00:00:53,259 --> 00:00:55,619
So it's just I don't do it too much because, honestly,

20
00:00:55,799 --> 00:00:57,140
setting into targets is, like,

21
00:00:57,140 --> 00:01:01,259
one thing that, again, is not always the measure,

22
00:01:01,439 --> 00:01:02,479
but it's kind of fun.

23
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:05,379
It puts a little bit of pressure on the setter to see if they keep their

24
00:01:05,379 --> 00:01:07,659
technique and they put work in that in situations.

25
00:01:08,739 --> 00:01:11,060
And it's a great reception game, a three-big-point game,

26
00:01:11,159 --> 00:01:12,260
because it's very competitive.

27
00:01:12,620 --> 00:01:13,799
There's a lot of pressure in that.

28
00:01:14,659 --> 00:01:17,060
And you've got to get three in a row to get a big point.

29
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:18,980
And once you get to three big points, you are the winner.

30
00:01:19,420 --> 00:01:20,019
And that's it.

31
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:20,640
That's the game we play.

32
00:01:23,489 --> 00:01:25,409
And we serve and we run to the other side.

33
00:01:25,530 --> 00:01:28,969
And very often, sorry, yeah, we serve and then you run to the other side

34
00:01:28,969 --> 00:01:29,329
and you get a good point.

35
00:01:29,329 --> 00:01:30,290
We're serving from both sides.

36
00:01:30,370 --> 00:01:33,090
And very often I say that they have to serve from one and one

37
00:01:33,090 --> 00:01:35,689
and then from five and five so that, again, we're varying our position.

38
00:01:36,810 --> 00:01:39,290
I've got to give that instruction or they forget because players can't

39
00:01:39,290 --> 00:01:39,730
remember everything.

